=======================
CSS Borders
=======================
The CSS border properties allow you to specify the style, width, and color of an element's border

properties:
**************
1. border-style 
    dotted, dashed, solid, double, groove, ridge, inset, outset, none, hidden

2. border-width
    -px, em etc 

    -The border-width property can have from one to four values (for the top border, right border, bottom border, and the left border)

    -border-width: 5px 20px; /* 5px top and bottom, 20px on the sides */

    -border-width: 25px 10px 4px 35px; /* 25px top, 10px right, 4px bottom and 35px left  trbl*/

3. border-color 
***********************
The border-color property is used to set the color of the four borders.The color can be set by:
    name - specify a color name, like "red"
    HEX - specify a HEX value, like "#ff0000"
    RGB - specify a RGB value, like "rgb(255,0,0)"
    HSL - specify a HSL value, like "hsl(0, 100%, 50%)"
    transparent
p.one {
  border-style: solid;
  border-color: red;
  border-color: #ff0000; /* red */
}

SPECIFIC STYLE OF BORDER
###############################
p {
  border-top-style: dotted;
  border-right-style: solid;
  border-bottom-style: dotted;
  border-left-style: solid;
}

border: Shorthand of border-width border-style border-color
********************
p {
  border: 5px solid red;
}

CSS Rounded Borders
***********************************
The border-radius property is used to add rounded borders to an element:
p {
  border: 2px solid red;
  border-radius: 5px;
}
